# SECURITY IS NON-NEGOTIABLE

## Input Validation
- Validate ALL inputs server-side with Zod (never trust client only)
- Use Drizzle ORM — NEVER concatenate user input into SQL
- Validate file uploads: type, size, content

## Authentication & Authorization
- Every tRPC mutation must check auth (protectedProcedure, federationAdminProcedure, adminProcedure)
- RBAC enforced at API level
- Session timeout handled by Supabase Auth

## Database Security
- RLS enabled on every Supabase table
- Test RLS policies
- Never expose service_role key in client bundles

## API Security
- CORS restrict to production domains
- Security headers: CSP, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options
- Generic error messages to clients; log details server-side
- Never expose stack traces in production

## Secrets Management
- All secrets in environment variables
- Document every env var in .env.example
- Different secrets per environment
